{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882014438,"sessionID":"ses_2852f1dbaffeMDrSEdD2QRiCsO","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad1061f001WqWjChNRKoQpUB","messageID":"msg_d7ad0fad20015U1n6bkr1XYQit","sessionID":"ses_2852f1dbaffeMDrSEdD2QRiCsO","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_bbf543e7591c43978c8645e5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-032/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-032/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** docker  \n4: **Language:** Dockerfile  \n5: **Size:** S  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Workload Manager Dockerfile\n11: \n12: - [ ] **T1.1** Create docker/Dockerfile with multi-stage build structure\n13:   - Set Stage 1: `FROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder`\n14:   - Set Stage 2: `FROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime`\n15:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n16:   - Verify: Both stages are defined with correct base images\n17: \n18: - [ ] **T1.2** Configure builder stage workdir and module caching\n19:   - Set `WORKDIR /build`\n20:   - Copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first\n21:   - Run `go mod download`\n22:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n23:   - Verify: Go modules cached before source code copy\n24: \n25: - [ ] **T1.3** Copy source code for Workload Manager\n26:   - Copy `cmd/workload-manager` to builder\n27:   - Copy `pkg` directory to builder\n28:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n29:   - Verify: Source files available in builder stage\n30: \n31: - [ ] **T1.4** Build static Workload Manager binary\n32:   - Set `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64`\n33:   - Use `-ldflags=\"-w -s\"` for binary optimization\n34:   - Output to `/build/workloadmanager`\n35:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n36:   - Verify: Binary compiled successfully in builder stage\n37: \n38: - [ ] **T1.5** Configure runtime stage with CA certificates\n39:   - Run `apk --no-cache add ca-certificates`\n40:   - Set `WORKDIR /app`\n41:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n42:   - Verify: CA certificates installed for HTTPS\n43: \n44: - [ ] **T1.6** Copy binary from builder to runtime\n45:   - Use `COPY --from=builder /build/workloadmanager /app/workloadmanager`\n46:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n47:   - Verify: Binary present in runtime image\n48: \n49: - [ ] **T1.7** Create non-root user for Workload Manager\n50:   - Create user `apiserver` with UID 1000\n51:   - Use Alpine `adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver`\n52:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n53:   - Verify: User created successfully\n54: \n55: - [ ] **T1.8** Set file ownership and switch to non-root user\n56:   - Run `chown -R apiserver:apiserver /app`\n57:   - Set `USER apiserver`\n58:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n59:   - Verify: Container runs as non-root (UID 1000)\n60: \n61: - [ ] **T1.9** Expose port and configure health check\n62:   - Add `EXPOSE 8080`\n63:   - Add HEALTHCHECK with `--interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3`\n64:   - Health check command: `wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1`\n65:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n66:   - Verify: Port 8080 exposed and health check configured\n67: \n68: - [ ] **T1.10** Add OCI labels and entrypoint\n69:   - Add labels: `org.opencontainers.image.title`, `org.opencontainers.image.description`, `org.opencontainers.image.vendor`\n70:   - Set `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]`\n71:   - Set `CMD [\"--port=8080\"]`\n72:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n73:   - Verify: Labels present and entrypoint configured\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## Phase 2: Router Dockerfile\n78: \n79: - [ ] **T2.1** Create docker/Dockerfile.router with multi-stage build structure\n80:   - Set Stage 1: `FROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder`\n81:   - Set Stage 2: `FROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime`\n82:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n83:   - Verify: Both stages defined with correct base images\n84: \n85: - [ ] **T2.2** Configure builder stage workdir and module caching\n86:   - Set `WORKDIR /build`\n87:   - Copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first\n88:   - Run `go mod download`\n89:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n90:   - Verify: Go modules cached before source code copy\n91: \n92: - [ ] **T2.3** Copy source code for Router\n93:   - Copy `cmd/router` to builder\n94:   - Copy `pkg` directory to builder\n95:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n96:   - Verify: Source files available in builder stage\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T2.4** Build static Router binary\n99:   - Set `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64`\n100:   - Use `-ldflags=\"-w -s\"` for binary optimization\n101:   - Output to `/build/router`\n102:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n103:   - Verify: Binary compiled successfully in builder stage\n104: \n105: - [ ] **T2.5** Configure runtime stage with CA certificates\n106:   - Run `apk --no-cache add ca-certificates`\n107:   - Set `WORKDIR /app`\n108:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n109:   - Verify: CA certificates installed for HTTPS\n110: \n111: - [ ] **T2.6** Copy binary from builder to runtime\n112:   - Use `COPY --from=builder /build/router /app/router`\n113:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n114:   - Verify: Binary present in runtime image\n115: \n116: - [ ] **T2.7** Create non-root user for Router\n117:   - Create user `router` with UID 1000\n118:   - Use Alpine `adduser -D -u 1000 router`\n119:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n120:   - Verify: User created successfully\n121: \n122: - [ ] **T2.8** Set file ownership and switch to non-root user\n123:   - Run `chown -R router:router /app`\n124:   - Set `USER router`\n125:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n126:   - Verify: Container runs as non-root (UID 1000)\n127: \n128: - [ ] **T2.9** Expose port and configure health check\n129:   - Add `EXPOSE 8080`\n130:   - Add HEALTHCHECK with `--interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3`\n131:   - Health check command: `wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1`\n132:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n133:   - Verify: Port 8080 exposed and health check configured\n134: \n135: - [ ] **T2.10** Add OCI labels and entrypoint\n136:   - Add labels: `org.opencontainers.image.title`, `org.opencontainers.image.description`, `org.opencontainers.image.vendor`\n137:   - Set `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/router\"]`\n138:   - Set `CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]`\n139:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n140:   - Verify: Labels present and entrypoint configured\n141: \n142: ---\n143: \n144: ## Phase 3: Picod Dockerfile\n145: \n146: - [ ] **T3.1** Create docker/Dockerfile.picod with multi-stage build structure\n147:   - Set Stage 1: `FROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder`\n148:   - Set Stage 2: `FROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime`\n149:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n150:   - Verify: Both stages defined with correct base images\n151: \n152: - [ ] **T3.2** Configure builder stage workdir and module caching\n153:   - Set `WORKDIR /build`\n154:   - Copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first\n155:   - Run `go mod download`\n156:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n157:   - Verify: Go modules cached before source code copy\n158: \n159: - [ ] **T3.3** Copy source code for Picod\n160:   - Copy `cmd/picod` to builder\n161:   - Copy `pkg` directory to builder\n162:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n163:   - Verify: Source files available in builder stage\n164: \n165: - [ ] **T3.4** Build static Picod binary\n166:   - Set `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64`\n167:   - Use `-ldflags=\"-w -s\"` for binary optimization\n168:   - Output to `/build/picod`\n169:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n170:   - Verify: Binary compiled successfully in builder stage\n171: \n172: - [ ] **T3.5** Configure runtime stage with CA certificates\n173:   - Run `apk --no-cache add ca-certificates`\n174:   - Set `WORKDIR /app`\n175:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n176:   - Verify: CA certificates installed for HTTPS\n177: \n178: - [ ] **T3.6** Copy binary from builder to runtime\n179:   - Use `COPY --from=builder /build/picod /app/picod`\n180:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n181:   - Verify: Binary present in runtime image\n182: \n183: - [ ] **T3.7** Create non-root user for Picod\n184:   - Create user `picod` with UID 1000\n185:   - Use Alpine `adduser -D -u 1000 picod`\n186:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n187:   - Verify: User created successfully\n188: \n189: - [ ] **T3.8** Set file ownership and switch to non-root user\n190:   - Run `chown -R picod:picod /app`\n191:   - Set `USER picod`\n192:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n193:   - Verify: Container runs as non-root (UID 1000)\n194: \n195: - [ ] **T3.9** Expose port and configure health check\n196:   - Add `EXPOSE 8080`\n197:   - Add HEALTHCHECK with `--interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3`\n198:   - Health check command: `wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1`\n199:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n200:   - Verify: Port 8080 exposed and health check configured\n201: \n202: - [ ] **T3.10** Add OCI labels and entrypoint\n203:   - Add labels: `org.opencontainers.image.title`, `org.opencontainers.image.description`, `org.opencontainers.image.vendor`\n204:   - Set `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/picod\"]`\n205:   - Set `CMD [\"--port=8080\"]`\n206:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n207:   - Verify: Labels present and entrypoint configured\n208: \n209: ---\n210: \n211: ## Phase 4: .dockerignore Configuration\n212: \n213: - [ ] **T4.1** Create docker/.dockerignore with version control exclusions\n214:   - Exclude `.git/`, `.gitignore`\n215:   - File: `docker/.dockerignore`\n216:   - Verify: Git files excluded from build context\n217: \n218: - [ ] **T4.2** Add build artifact exclusions\n219:   - Exclude `bin/`, `dist/`, `*.out`, `coverage.out`\n220:   - File: `docker/.dockerignore`\n221:   - Verify: Build artifacts excluded from context\n222: \n223: - [ ] **T4.3** Add test and documentation exclusions\n224:   - Exclude `testing/`, `*_test.go`, `*.md` (except README.md)\n225:   - File: `docker/.dockerignore`\n226:   - Verify: Test files and docs excluded from context\n227: \n228: - [ ] **T4.4** Add IDE and development file exclusions\n229:   - Exclude `.idea/`, `.vscode/`, `*.swp`, `*.swo`, `*~`\n230:   - Exclude `.pytest_cache/`, `__pycache__/`, `*.pyc`\n231:   - File: `docker/.dockerignore`\n232:   - Verify: IDE and Python artifacts excluded\n233: \n234: - [ ] **T4.5** Add Docker and manifest exclusions\n235:   - Exclude `docker/`, `Dockerfile*`, `manifests/`, `changes/`\n236:   - File: `docker/.dockerignore`\n237:   - Verify: Docker files and manifests excluded to prevent recursive copy\n238: \n239: ---\n240: \n241: ## Phase 5: Makefile Integration\n242: \n243: - [ ] **T5.1** Add Docker configuration variables to Makefile\n244:   - Add `DOCKER_REGISTRY ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh`\n245:   - Add `DOCKER_TAG ?= latest`\n246:   - Add `VERSION`, `COMMIT_SHA` variables\n247:   - Add image name variables for all three components\n248:   - File: `Makefile`\n249:   - Verify: Variables defined correctly\n250: \n251: - [ ] **T5.2** Create docker-build-workloadmanager target\n252:   - Build with `docker/Dockerfile`\n253:   - Tag with `DOCKER_TAG`, `COMMIT_SHA`, `VERSION`\n254:   - File: `Makefile`\n255:   - Verify: `make docker-build-workloadmanager` builds image\n256: \n257: - [ ] **T5.3** Create docker-build-router target\n258:   - Build with `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n259:   - Tag with `DOCKER_TAG`, `COMMIT_SHA`, `VERSION`\n260:   - File: `Makefile`\n261:   - Verify: `make docker-build-router` builds image\n262: \n263: - [ ] **T5.4** Create docker-build-picod target\n264:   - Build with `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n265:   - Tag with `DOCKER_TAG`, `COMMIT_SHA`, `VERSION`\n266:   - File: `Makefile`\n267:   - Verify: `make docker-build-picod` builds image\n268: \n269: - [ ] **T5.5** Create docker-build-all target\n270:   - Depends on all three build targets\n271:   - File: `Makefile`\n272:   - Verify: `make docker-build-all` builds all images sequentially\n273: \n274: - [ ] **T5.6** Create push targets for all images\n275:   - Create `docker-push-workloadmanager`, `docker-push-router`, `docker-push-picod`\n276:   - Create `docker-push-all` aggregate target\n277:   - File: `Makefile`\n278:   - Verify: Push targets use correct registry and tags\n279: \n280: - [ ] **T5.7** Create kind-load targets (optional)\n281:   - Create `kind-load-workloadmanager`, `kind-load-router`, `kind-load-picod`\n282:   - Create `kind-load-all` aggregate target\n283:   - File: `Makefile`\n284:   - Verify: Images loadable to Kind cluster\n285: \n286: - [ ] **T5.8** Create docker-clean target\n287:   - Remove local images with all tags\n288:   - Use `-` prefix to ignore errors\n289:   - File: `Makefile`\n290:   - Verify: `make docker-clean` removes images safely\n291: \n292: ---\n293: \n294: ## Phase 6: Dockerfile Validation\n295: \n296: - [ ] **T6.1** Build Workload Manager image\n297:   - Command: `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t workloadmanager:test .`\n298:   - Verify: Build completes without errors\n299:   - Verify: Image created with tag `workloadmanager:test`\n300: \n301: - [ ] **T6.2** Build Router image\n302:   - Command: `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t router:test .`\n303:   - Verify: Build completes without errors\n304:   - Verify: Image created with tag `router:test`\n305: \n306: - [ ] **T6.3** Build Picod image\n307:   - Command: `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.picod -t picod:test .`\n308:   - Verify: Build completes without errors\n309:   - Verify: Image created with tag `picod:test`\n310: \n311: - [ ] **T6.4** Verify image sizes under 50MB\n312:   - Command: `docker images workloadmanager:test router:test picod:test`\n313:   - Verify: All images < 50MB\n314:   - Verify: Sizes approximately 25-35MB each\n315: \n316: - [ ] **T6.5** Verify non-root user execution\n317:   - Command: `docker run --rm workloadmanager:test id -u`\n318:   - Command: `docker run --rm router:test id -u`\n319:   - Command: `docker run --rm picod:test id -u`\n320:   - Verify: All return UID 1000 (not root)\n321: \n322: - [ ] **T6.6** Verify port 8080 exposed\n323:   - Command: `docker inspect workloadmanager:test --format='{{.Config.ExposedPorts}}'`\n324:   - Verify: Port 8080/tcp listed for all images\n325: \n326: - [ ] **T6.7** Verify health check configured\n327:   - Command: `docker inspect workloadmanager:test --format='{{.Config.Healthcheck}}'`\n328:   - Verify: Health check present with correct intervals\n329: \n330: - [ ] **T6.8** Verify OCI labels present\n331:   - Command: `docker inspect workloadmanager:test --format='{{.Config.Labels}}'`\n332:   - Verify: Labels include title, description, vendor for all images\n333: \n334: - [ ] **T6.9** Verify static binary linkage\n335:   - Command: `docker run --rm workloadmanager:test /app/workloadmanager --help` (or similar)\n336:   - Verify: Binary runs without dynamic library errors\n337: \n338: - [ ] **T6.10** Verify layer count ≤ 5\n339:   - Command: `docker history workloadmanager:test`\n340:   - Verify: Layer count ≤ 5 for all images\n341: \n342: ---\n343: \n344: ## Phase 7: Make Target Testing\n345: \n346: - [ ] **T7.1** Test docker-build-all target\n347:   - Command: `make docker-build-all`\n348:   - Verify: All three images build successfully\n349:   - Verify: Images tagged with `latest` tag\n350: \n351: - [ ] **T7.2** Test docker-build-all with custom tag\n352:   - Command: `make docker-build-all DOCKER_TAG=v1.0.0`\n353:   - Verify: Images tagged with `v1.0.0`\n354: \n355: - [ ] **T7.3** Test docker-build-all with commit SHA tag\n356:   - Command: `make docker-build-all COMMIT_SHA=$(git rev-parse --short HEAD)`\n357:   - Verify: Images tagged with actual commit SHA\n358: \n359: - [ ] **T7.4** Test docker-clean target\n360:   - Command: `make docker-clean`\n361:   - Verify: Images removed (or error ignored if not present)\n362: \n363: ---\n364: \n365: ## Phase 8: Container Runtime Testing (Optional)\n366: \n367: - [ ] **T8.1** Test Workload Manager container startup\n368:   - Command: `docker run -d --name wm-test -p 8080:8080 workloadmanager:test`\n369:   - Wait 10 seconds for startup\n370:   - Command: `docker inspect wm-test --format='{{.State.Running}}'`\n371:   - Verify: Container running\n372:   - Cleanup: `docker stop wm-test && docker rm wm-test`\n373: \n374: - [ ] **T8.2** Test Router container startup\n375:   - Command: `docker run -d --name router-test -p 8081:8080 -e REDIS_ADDR=redis:6379 router:test`\n376:   - Wait 10 seconds for startup\n377:   - Command: `docker inspect router-test --format='{{.State.Running}}'`\n378:   - Verify: Container running\n379:   - Cleanup: `docker stop router-test && docker rm router-test`\n380: \n381: - [ ] **T8.3** Test Picod container startup\n382:   - Command: `docker run -d --name picod-test -p 8082:8080 picod:test`\n383:   - Wait 10 seconds for startup\n384:   - Command: `docker inspect picod-test --format='{{.State.Running}}'`\n385:   - Verify: Container running\n386:   - Cleanup: `docker stop picod-test && docker rm picod-test`\n387: \n388: ---\n389: \n390: ## Acceptance Criteria\n391: \n392: 1. ✅ `docker/Dockerfile` — Workload Manager multi-stage build complete\n393: 2. ✅ `docker/Dockerfile.router` — Router multi-stage build complete\n394: 3. ✅ `docker/Dockerfile.picod` — Picod multi-stage build complete\n395: 4. ✅ `docker/.dockerignore` — Build context optimization configured\n396: 5. ✅ All Dockerfiles use `golang:1.21-alpine` as builder base\n397: 6. ✅ All Dockerfiles use `alpine:3.19` as runtime base\n398: 7. ✅ Go modules cached before source code copy (optimization)\n399: 8. ✅ Static binaries compiled with `CGO_ENABLED=0`\n400: 9. ✅ Non-root user (UID 1000) created in all runtime images\n401: 10. ✅ All images expose port 8080\n402: 11. ✅ All images have health check configured\n403: 12. ✅ All images have OCI labels (title, description, vendor)\n404: 13. ✅ All images have correct entrypoint and CMD\n405: 14. ✅ Image sizes under 50MB each\n406: 15. ✅ Layer count ≤ 5 for all images\n407: 16. ✅ Makefile targets for build, push, and clean operations\n408: 17. ✅ `make docker-build-all` builds all three images\n409: 18. ✅ Makefile supports custom DOCKER_TAG and COMMIT_SHA\n410: 19. ✅ `.dockerignore` excludes unnecessary files from build context\n411: 20. ✅ All containers run as non-root user (verified with `id -u`)\n412: \n413: ---\n414: \n415: **Notes:**\n416: - Stage ST-3: Implementation complete (Dockerfiles and Makefile targets created)\n417: - Three separate Dockerfiles for three components (Workload Manager, Router, Picod)\n418: - Multi-stage build pattern: builder (Go) → runtime (Alpine)\n419: - Security: Non-root execution, minimal base image, static binaries\n420: - Optimization: Go module caching, `.dockerignore` for context size reduction\n421: - Expected image sizes: 25-35MB each\n422: - Makefile integration provides consistent build/push workflow\n\n(End of file - total 422 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) Tasks\n\n**Module:** docker  \n**Language:** Dockerfile  \n**Size:** S  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Workload Manager Dockerfile\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Create docker/Dockerfile with multi-stage build structure\n  - Set Stage 1: `FROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder`\n  - Set Stage 2: `FROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n  - Verify: Both stages are defined with correct base images\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Configure builder stage workdir and module caching\n  - Set `WORKDIR /build`\n  - Copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-032/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775882014389,"end":1775882014435}}}}
